==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Xylography
<hw>Xy*log"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Xylo-</ets> + <ets>-graphy</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>xylographie</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of engraving on wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The art of making prints from the natural grain of
wood.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A method pf printing in colors upon wood for
purposes of house decoration.</def> <rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Xyloid</ent>⟦br⟧
